'''Marc Anthony Pugh'''<ref name="Marc Pugh playerhistory">{{cite web
| title = Marc Pugh
| url = http://playerhistory.com/Default.aspx?page=player_details&playerID=86285
| publisher = Playerhistory
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> (born 2 April 1987) is an English [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] in [[Football League Two|League Two]] as a [[midfielder]]. He plays mainly as an [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]] but can also play as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] and as a [[striker]].

Pugh started his career with [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], where he progressed through the youth ranks. He was released by the club before being able to make his debut for the first-team and signed a short-term contract with [[Bury F.C.|Bury]]. He later signed a professional contract at the club and he later rejected an extended contract, eventually signing for Shrewsbury Town.

==Career==
===Burnley===
Pugh was born on 2 April 1987 in [[Bacup]], [[Lancashire]] and attended [[All Saints Catholic Language College]] in [[Rawtenstall]].<ref name="Marc Pugh soccerbase">{{cite web
| title = Marc Pugh
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/players_details.sd?playerid=38008
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref><ref name="Late goal for ten man reserves">{{cite news
| first = Peter
| last = Heywood
| title = Late goal for ten man reserves
| url = http://www.clarets-mad.co.uk/news/loadroll.asp?cid=ED31&id=101412
| publisher = Clarets MAD
| date = 2003-04-23
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> He started his [[association football|footballing]] career with [[Football League Championship|Championship]] side [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] where, at a young age, he started as a Centre of Excellence player, and gradually worked his way up through the ranks to becoming a footballing apprentice in 2003.<ref name="Marc Pugh goes out to Kidderminster">{{cite news | title=Marc Pugh goes out to Kidderminster | publisher=thefootballnetwork.net | url=http://www.sportnetwork.net/main/s37/st85191.htm?fromrss=1 | date=2005-11-10 }}</ref> As a first year apprentice he played for the youth and reserve teams and due to his great goalscoring record, which led him to be named on the bench for two first-team matches in the [[Football League Cup|League Cup]], they decided to keep him on for a third year.<ref name="Marc Pugh goes out to Kidderminster"/> As a third year apprentice he scored 15 goals for the club's reserve and youth team.<ref name="Pugh gets deal">{{cite news | first=Tony | last=Scholes | title=Pugh gets deal | publisher=Clarets MAD | url=http://www.clarets-mad.co.uk/news/loadnews.asp?cid=TMNW&id=282980 | date=2006-05-16}}</ref> This led to him to being sent out on loan to [[Kidderminster Harriers F.C.|Kidderminster Harriers]] in the [[Conference National]] in November 2005 to gain first-team football.<ref name="Kidderminster agree deal for Pugh">{{cite news
| title = Kidderminster agree deal for Pugh
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/k/kidderminster_harriers/4424424.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-11-10
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> He made his debut for Kidderminster after coming on as a 86th minute substitute in a 3&ndash;1 defeat to [[Stevenage Borough F.C.|Stevenage Borough]].<ref name="Stevenage 3-1 Kidderminster">{{cite news
| title = Stevenage 3-1 Kidderminster
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4427476.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-11-12
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> He converted a [[Simon Heslop]] cross during a match against [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] to score his first career goal, which helped Kidderminster to a 3&ndash;1 victory.<ref name="Kidderminster 3-1 Dag & Red">{{cite news
| title = Kidderminster 3-1 Dag & Red
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_conf/4472998.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-12-03
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> Also, during a match he displayed a smart piece of skill which involved flicking the ball over an opponents head with his heel, then crossing the ball in for a teammate to score; this move was featured on [[Soccer AM]]'s [[showboat]]ing section.<ref name="Marc Pugh shrewsbury town">{{cite news
| title = Marc Pugh
| url = http://www.shrewsburytown.com/page/QandA/0,,10443~1146115,00.html
| publisher = Shrewsbury Town F.C.
| date = 2007-10-18
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> He returned to Burnley on 13 December after picking up a [[groin]] injury,<ref name="Pugh returns from Harriers spell december 2005">{{cite news
| title = Pugh returns from Harriers spell
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/burnley/4523850.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2005-12-13
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> but eventually returned for a second spell on 7 January 2006.<ref name="Pugh Resumes Harriers Spell">{{cite news
| title = Pugh Resumes Harriers Spell
| url = http://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/page/LatestHeadlines/0,,10413~765006,00.html
| publisher = Burnley F.C.
| date = 2006-01-07
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> This spell ended on 26 January so Pugh could concentrate on his career at Burnley and made 10 appearances and scored one goal while at Kidderminster.<ref name="Pugh returns from Harriers spell january 2006">{{cite news
| title = Pugh returns from Harriers spell
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/burnley/4650330.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2006-01-26
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref><ref name="Kidderminster 2005/2006 player appearances">{{cite web
| title = Kidderminster 2005/2006 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?seasonid=135&teamid=1436
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> He learned that he would not receive a professional contract at Burnley in February, which was partly because both [[Chris McCann (footballer)|Chris McCann]] and [[Kyle Lafferty]] had both already received professional contracts and they were only second year apprentices.<ref name="Youth Team News">{{cite news
| title = Youth Team News
| url = http://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/page/LatestHeadlines/0,,10413~795034,00.html
| publisher = Burnley F.C.
| date = 2006-02-27
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref>

===Bury===
Having just been released from Burnley, Pugh started looking for a new club, and was eventually offered a place at [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Bury F.C.|Bury]] on a short-term contract following a three week long trial at the club.<ref name="Shakers capture midfield quartet">{{cite news
| title = Shakers capture midfield quartet
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bury/4836832.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2006-03-23
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref><ref name="Shakers sign Pugh">{{cite news
| title = Shakers sign Pugh
| url = http://archive.lancashireeveningtelegraph.co.uk/2006/3/24/890500.html
| publisher = Lancashire Evening Telegraph
| date = 2006-03-24
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> Bury were entangled in a relegation battle and Pugh made his debut after coming on as an 80th minute substitute [[Lewis Gobern]] in a 2&ndash;1 win against [[Rochdale A.F.C.|Rochdale]] on 25 March.<ref name="Bury 2-1 Rochdale">{{cite news
| title = Bury 2-1 Rochdale
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/4819762.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2006-03-25
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> He marked his first start for Bury with goal in the 1&ndash;1 draw against [[Lincoln City F.C.|Lincoln City]] on 15 April,<ref name="Lincoln City 1-1 Bury">{{cite news
| title = Lincoln City 1-1 Bury
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/4890980.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2006-04-14
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> after which manager [[Chris Casper]] commented "Mark's a good player and he's got a bright future if he keeps his feet on the ground".<ref name="Casper pays tribute to Pugh">{{cite news | title=Casper pays tribute to Pugh | publisher=Manchester Evening News | url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/bury/s/210/210848_casper_pays_tribute_to_pugh.html| date=2006-04-17}}</ref> He finished the [[2005–06 in English football|2005&ndash;06]] season by playing six games and scoring one goal for the club.<ref name="Bury 2005/2006 player appearances">{{cite web
| title = Bury 2005/2006 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?seasonid=135&teamid=394
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> As a result of his good performances (and helped by the fact that Bury had survived relegation), Bury manager Chris Casper offered him a new one-year contract at [[Gigg Lane]]; his first professional contract.<ref name="Three Extend at Gigg">{{cite news
| title = Three Extend at Gigg
| url = http://www.buryfc.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10422~832460,00.html
| publisher = Bury F.C.
| date = 2006-05-23
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> Pugh was very much a regular first-team player in the [[2006–07 in English football|2006&ndash;07]] season, playing particularly well in the first half of the season and was offered an extended contract at the club,<ref name="Contracts on cards for Shakers duo">{{cite news
| title = Contracts on cards for Shakers duo
| url = http://www.buryfc.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10422~966896,00.html
| publisher = Bury F.C.
| date = 2006-01-18
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> which Pugh rejected, saying he "wanted to keep his options open".<ref name="Pugh rejects new Bury contract">{{cite news | title=Pugh rejects new Bury contract | publisher=BBC Sport | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bury/6362161.stm | date =2007-02-14}}</ref> Manager Chris Casper revealed his disappointment at this and Pugh later said financial reasons were not behind his motivation to reject a new contract.<ref name="Casper 'let down' by contract rebel Pugh">{{cite news
| title = Casper 'let down' by contract rebel Pugh
| url = http://www.buryfc.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10422~982967,00.html
| publisher = Bury F.C.
| date = 2007-02-16
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref><ref name="Money not reason for deal delay - Pugh">{{cite news
| title = Money not reason for deal delay - Pugh
| url = http://www.buryfc.co.uk/page/LatestNews/0,,10422~983880,00.html
| publisher = Bury F.C.
| date = 2007-02-19
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> He was offered renewed contracts throughout the season but still took none of them, with Casper blaming his agent for this.<ref name="Pugh signs for Shrews">{{cite news | first=Tony| last=Scholes| title=Pugh signs for Shrews | publisher=Clarets MAD | url=http://www.claretsmad.co.uk/news/loadnews.asp?cid=TMNW&id=339771 |date=2007-05-29}}</ref>

===Shrewsbury Town===
With many clubs interested in his services,<ref name="Pugh signs for Shrews"/> Pugh eventually signed for fellow League Two side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] on 29 May 2007 for a fee that would be decided by a tribunal.<ref name="Shrews complete signing of trio">{{cite news | title=Shrews complete signing of trio | publisher=BBC Sport | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/shrewsbury/6703637.stm | date = 2007-05-30 | accessdate = 2007-05-30}}</ref> Shrewsbury manager [[Gary Peters (footballer)|Gary Peters]] revealed that he had already attempted to sign him earlier in the season as part of a swap deal when striker [[Glynn Hurst]] moved to Bury.<ref name="Pugh signs for Shrews"/> He made his debut in a 4&ndash;0 victory over Lincoln City, setting up [[Andy Cooke]] for the the third goal with a cross.<ref name="Lincoln 0-4 Shrewsbury">{{cite news
| title = Lincoln 0-4 Shrewsbury
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/6931021.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2007-08-11
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> He suffered from an injury in November and underwent a scan, which was believed to be a [[cartilage]] problem.<ref name="Tudor and Pugh">{{cite news
| title = Tudor and Pugh
| url = http://www.shrewsburytown.com/page/NewsDetail/0,,10443~1177136,00.html
| publisher = Shrewsbury Town F.C.
| date = 2007-11-27
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> Days after discovering the results of the scan, which revealed he was sufferig from acute [[tendinitis]], he returned to training,<ref name="Pugh returns to Shrews' training">{{cite news
| title = Pugh returns to Shrews' training
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/s/shrewsbury/7138692.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2007-12-11
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> and scored his first goal for Shrewsbury on his return in a 4&ndash;0 victory over [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]].<ref name="Shrewsbury 4-0 Dag & Red">{{cite news
| title = Shrewsbury 4-0 Dag & Red
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7134235.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2007-12-15
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> He went on to score a further two goals that season following the arrival of [[Paul Simpson (footballer)|Paul Simpson]] as manager, and finished the [[2007–08 in English football|2007&ndash;08]] season with 38 appearances and four goals.<ref name="Shrewsbury 2007/2008 player appearances">{{cite web
| title = Shrewsbury 2007/2008 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?seasonid=137&teamid=2325
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref>

After struggling to feature in the team at the start of the [[2008–09 in English football|2008&ndash;09]] season,<ref name="Player Out On Loan">{{cite news
| title = Player Out On Loan
| url = http://www.shrewsburytown.com/page/NewsDetail/0,,10443~1389655,00.html
| publisher = Shrewsbury Town F.C.
| date = 2008-09-12
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> he joined fellow League Two side [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] on a month's loan on 12 September 2008.<ref name="Luton sign Shrews winger on loan">{{cite news
| title = Luton sign Shrews winger on loan
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/luton_town/7611766.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-09-12
| accessdate = 2008-12-16}}</ref> His debut came in a 3&ndash;1 victory over [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]],<ref name="Luton 3-1 Aldershot">{{cite news
| title = Luton 3-1 Aldershot
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_3/7602070.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-09-13
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> after which manager [[Mick Harford]] said "He is an out and out winger, and he put in some good crosses. But he hasn't played a lot of football this season and he maybe faded a bit".<ref name="Brill warned to fight for place">{{cite news
| title = Brill warned to fight for place
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/luton_town/7616711.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = 2008-09-15
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref> He returned to Shrewsbury after playing four games in a Luton shirt.<ref name="Luton 2008/2009 player appearances">{{cite web
| title = Luton 2008/2009 player appearances
| url = http://www.soccerbase.com/squad_season.sd?seasonid=138&teamid=1628
| publisher = Soccerbase
| accessdate = 2008-12-17}}</ref>

